<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="144" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d144">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">710.11/12–1245: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dawson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-12">December 12,
                                1945</date>.<lb/>[Received December 12—9:41 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>788. After all-night debate Senate rejected this morning by 16 to 15 a
                            motion disapproving Foreign Minister’s initiative. Details later.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>